{#

This file extends from the 'Card' organism.

What we are doing here is checking if a field has a 'value' via the 'paragraph'
object. If we use the 'content' object, the render array will always return
something.

Once we know a field has a value, we then set a new variable using the render
array of that field. We need to do this as we only want to pass it to PatternLab
if the field is not empty.

We then pass the newly created variable to PatternLab.

#}

{% if paragraph.field_p_card_title.value %}
  {% set card_title = content.field_p_card_title %}
{% endif %}

{% if paragraph.field_p_card_text.value %}
  {% set card_text = content.field_p_card_text %}
{% endif %}

{% if paragraph.field_p_card_image.value %}
  {% set card_image = content.field_p_card_image %}
{% endif %}

{% if paragraph.field_p_card_cta.value %}
  {% set card_cta = content.field_p_card_cta %}
{% endif %}

{% include "@building-blocks/card/card.twig"
  with {
    "title": card_title,
    "text": card_text,
    "image": card_image,
    "cta": card_cta
  }
%}
